member.remarks:
            Usage is:

            using (WaitCursorScope.Enter())
            {
                // perform UI activity
            }

            This pattern ensures:


The cursor is always restored when the block exits, whether by fall-through, return or exception.

Nested scopes work properly. That is, an inner scope doesn't reset the mouse when it exits.
            Only the top-most scope will fully restore the mouse cursor.
